|Description = [[Independent Communications Authority of South Africa|ICASA]] ordered that this photograph of a police officer firing rubber bullets at unarmed residents during a protest in [[Bekkersdal]] in March 2014 related to an [[African National Congress|ANC]] [[South African general election, 2014|2014 election]] campaign be removed from a [[Democratic Alliance (South Africa)|DA]] election campaign television advert.
|Source = [http://citizen.co.za/166103/icasa-upholds-saps-complaint-citizen-photo/ The Citizen website]
|Date = 13 March 2014
|Author = ''[[The Citizen (South Africa)|The Citizen]]'' photographer Alaister Russell
|Article = South African general election, 2014
|Purpose = To support encyclopedic discussion of this work in this article. The illustration is specifically needed to support the following point(s): <br/>
The photograph is ICASA's stated reason for banning a DA 2014 election campaign television advert.
